I gotta focus.

24
00:03:20,984 --> 00:03:22,383
Marry me.

25
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,746
No.

26
00:03:33,597 --> 00:03:34,962
Marry me.

27
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,069
Change me.

28
00:03:46,845 --> 00:03:48,745
Okay, I will if you marry me.

29
00:03:48,813 --> 00:03:50,974
It's called a compromise.

30
00:03:56,221 --> 00:03:58,519
Let's just call it coercion.

31
00:03:58,590 --> 00:04:00,148
It's not fair.

32
00:04:01,693 --> 00:04:03,820
Marriage is just...

33
00:04:03,895 --> 00:04:05,886
It's a piece of paper.

34
00:04:07,932 --> 00:04:11,265
Where I'm from,
it's the way one says, "I love you."

35
00:04:12,937 --> 00:04:16,134
Well, where I come from, at my age,

36
00:04:18,142 --> 00:04:21,168
it's the way one says,
"I just got knocked up."

37
00:04:24,415 --> 00:04:28,146
So, you're worried
about what people will think?

38
00:04:29,921 --> 00:04:33,255
You know,
two out of three marriages end in divorce.

39
00:04:34,393 --> 00:04:39,797
Well, I think you'll find
the vampirel human divorce rate

40
00:04:39,865 --> 00:04:41,662
is a little lower.

41
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:48,106
So marry me.

42
00:04:52,578 --> 00:04:53,977
I can't.

43
00:04:56,048 --> 00:04:58,175
I have to be back at 4:00.

44
00:05:16,435 --> 00:05:17,435
(DOOR CLOSING)

45
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:23,600
4:00 on the dot.

46
00:05:24,044 --> 00:05:27,104
That kid trying to brown-nose me now
or something?

47
00:05:27,814 --> 00:05:31,306
He has a name.
Now he's too punctual for you?

48
00:05:39,693 --> 00:05:40,887
Okay.

49
00:05:42,629 --> 00:05:44,995
You understand
why you're being punished, right?

50
00:05:45,665 --> 00:05:47,997
I know, I put you through hell.

51
00:05:48,068 --> 00:05:49,660
Yes, you did.

52
00:05:51,371 --> 00:05:54,397
But I have other reasons for grounding you.

53
00:05:54,474 --> 00:05:55,771
Like...

54
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:02,915
I just want you to get some separation
from him.

55
00:06:05,819 --> 00:06:08,344
Dad, there's nothing you can say.

56
00:06:10,758 --> 00:06:12,453
Edward is in my life.

57
00:06:14,962 --> 00:06:17,021
Yeah, I'm gathering that.

58
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:21,693
So, all right, how about this?

59
00:06:22,403 --> 00:06:24,303
I'll make you a deal.

60
00:06:25,339 --> 00:06:27,899
You're not grounded anymore

61
00:06:30,277 --> 00:06:35,146
if you use your new-found freedom to see
some of your other friends, too, like...

62
00:06:35,983 --> 00:06:37,007
Like Jacob.

63
00:06:37,818 --> 00:06:39,513
He's going through
a really tough time right now.

64
00:06:39,587 --> 00:06:41,782
His dad's really worried about him.

65
00:06:42,289 --> 00:06:44,587
I remember when that was you.

66
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:47,659
You needed a friend.

67
00:06:48,029 --> 00:06:49,621
Jake was there.

68
00:06:54,001 --> 00:06:56,435
(ON VOICE MAIL)
Hey, it's Jake. Leave a message.

69
