00:07:25,534 --> 00:07:28,435
♪ If just for tonight darling ♪

76
00:07:30,205 --> 00:07:32,503
♪ Let's get lost ♪

77
00:07:34,543 --> 00:07:38,843
♪ If just for tonight darling ♪

78
00:07:38,914 --> 00:07:41,439
♪ Let's get lost ♪

79
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:43,315
(ENGINE STALLING)

80
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,560
(CRASHING)

81
00:07:58,868 --> 00:08:00,495
You scared me.

82
00:08:03,673 --> 00:08:05,153
You're going down to the reservation.

83
00:08:06,175 --> 00:08:07,733
How did you...

84
00:08:08,211 --> 00:08:09,439
Alice.

85
00:08:12,949 --> 00:08:14,439
Hey, did you do this to my truck?

86
00:08:15,718 --> 00:08:17,743
Bella, you have to understand.

87
00:08:17,854 --> 00:08:19,583
Your safety is everything to me.

88
00:08:19,655 --> 00:08:21,088
Jacob's not gonna hurt me.

89
00:08:21,157 --> 00:08:23,887
Not intentionally,
but the wolves have no control.

90
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:24,984
Edward.

91
00:08:25,628 --> 00:08:29,359
I have until graduation to see him.

92
00:08:32,635 --> 00:08:34,660
And then I'll be one of you,

93
00:08:35,004 --> 00:08:36,471
and he'll hate me forever.

94
00:08:36,873 --> 00:08:38,569
Well, I'm sorry.

95
00:08:46,383 --> 00:08:47,850
(ALL CHATTERING)

96
00:08:50,554 --> 00:08:52,784
JESSICA: No way. Stop.
MIKE: Throw it away.

97
00:08:52,856 --> 00:08:54,187
Good.
Hey.

98
00:08:54,258 --> 00:08:56,818
Just in time. All right, check it out.
All right. Let's see, we got.

99
00:08:56,894 --> 00:08:59,419
"My fellow students." Right?
Good.

100
00:08:59,496 --> 00:09:01,794
Cute.
Right? "We are the future."

101
00:09:01,865 --> 00:09:04,163
"Anything is possible,
if you just believe."

102
00:09:04,234 --> 00:09:05,394
Nice.

103
00:09:06,303 --> 00:09:07,303
ERIC: Perfect.

104
00:09:07,371 --> 00:09:08,599
And you got yourself a speech.

105
00:09:08,672 --> 00:09:11,937
No, this'll be my speech when I want
everyone to throw diplomas at my head.

106
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,601
So, thank you.

107
00:09:15,379 --> 00:09:16,710
You gotta embrace the cliches, Jess.

108
00:09:16,780 --> 00:09:19,146
They are the bread and butter
of all valedictorians.

109
00:09:19,650 --> 00:09:21,777
And that is why you are not valedictorian.

110
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:23,979
Jess doesn't need cliches.

111
00:09:24,054 --> 00:09:25,174
The speech is gonna be epic.

112
00:09:25,957 --> 00:09:27,822
Epic? It'll change lives.

113
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:30,227
I've decided to throw a party.

114
00:09:31,129 --> 00:09:33,495
After all, how many times
are we gonna graduate high school?

115
00:09:34,232 --> 00:09:35,722
A party? At your place?

116
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:38,961
I've never seen your house.

117
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:40,561
No one's ever seen their house.

118
00:09:40,805 --> 00:09:42,329
Another party, Alice?

119
00:09:42,674 --> 00:09:43,766
It'll be fun.

120
00:09:43,842 --> 00:09:45,537
Yeah. That's what you said last time.

121
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:52,073
Hey, Angela.
Yeah?

122
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:53,470
Do you need some help with those?

123
00:09:59,157 --> 00:10:01,216
JESSICA: be sending money
'cause it's the polite thing to do,

124
00:10:01,292 --> 00:10:02,350
and then you'll be raking it in.

125
00:10:02,427 --> 00:10:04,452
MIKE: Wait a minute. People give you money?

126
00:10:18,143 --> 00:10:19,838
(INAUDIBLE)

127
00:10:23,549 --> 00:10:25,608
I know you know what she saw. Tell me.

128
00:10:25,885 --> 00:10:27,512
It was nothing.

129
00:10:28,554 --> 00:10:30,283
You looked worried.

130
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:34,657
Just that everyone noticed
how strange Alice is.

131
00:10:36,128 --> 00:10:38,096
I think that ship sailed long ago.

132
00:10:41,433 --> 00:10:43,298
I wonder what's wrong.

133
00:10:43,369 --> 00:10:46,133
EDWARD: Their son went missing in Seattle
over a year ago.

134
00:10:46,272 --> 00:10:48,866
Charlie's doing what he can, but...

135
00:10:51,810 --> 00:10:53,641
You know something about this?

136
00:10:56,749 --> 00:10:59,582
We've been tracking the situation
in Seattle for a while.

137
00:11:00,119 --> 00:11:02,986
Unexplained disappearances. Killings.

138
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:08,090
If the situation gets any more conspicuous,
the Volturi will step in.

139
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:12,157
If they go to Seattle,
they could come here.

140
00:11:12,232 --> 00:11:13,699
They could see I'm still human.

141
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:15,359
It won't get that far.

142
00:11:15,568 --> 00:11:18,298
But we'll go to Seattle if we have to.

143
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:23,034
CHARLIE: I'll fax these down, first thing.
MR. BIERS: Thank you.

144
00:11:24,177 --> 00:11:25,735
Hey.
Hey.

145
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,675
You ready for dinner?
Yeah.

146
00:11:30,016 --> 00:11:32,814
It is still just you and I, right?

147
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,218
No, I'm just dropping her off.

148
00:11:37,023 --> 00:11:38,081
See you later.

149
00:11:38,191 --> 00:11:39,351
Bye.

150
00:11:42,028 --> 00:11:45,486
Bella, my parents wanted to remind you
about the airline ticket

151
00:11:45,565 --> 00:11:48,534
you got for your birthday.
What airline ticket?

152
00:11:50,203 --> 00:11:52,832
A round trip ticket to see Mom in Florida.

153
00:11:53,774 --> 00:11:55,139
That was generous.

154
00:11:55,209 --> 00:11:57,643
It expires soon,
so you might want to use it this weekend.

155
00:11:57,712 --> 00:12:00,704
Well, I can't just drop everything and go.

156
00:12:01,415 --> 00:12:04,043
It might be your last chance to see her
before you graduate.

157
00:12:05,353 --> 00:12:07,253
CHARLIE: Might not be a bad idea.

158
00:12:07,321 --> 00:12:10,688
Get out of town for a couple days.
Get some distance.

159
00:12:11,993 --> 00:12:13,313
Yeah, I wouldn't mind seeing Mom.

160
00:12:15,096 --> 00:12:17,257
As long as you use the companion ticket.

161
00:12:17,331 --> 00:12:19,458
Wait. There's two tickets?

162
00:12:21,969 --> 00:12:23,300
Super.

163
00:12:23,637 --> 00:12:25,832
That makes me really happy.

164
00:12:28,409 --> 00:12:30,707
BELLA: I did want to see my mom.

165
00:12:30,778 --> 00:12:34,339
I wanted to know
that her life was full and satisfying.

166
00:12:36,584 --> 00:12:38,745
RENEE: Aren't you gonna miss this?

167
00:12:39,220 --> 00:12:42,622
Can't you just feel the vitamin D
soaking up in your pores?

168
00:12:46,395 --> 00:12:48,522
Yeah, I am gonna miss this.

169
00:12:50,532 --> 00:12:53,365
You know, colleges in Florida
are a lot sunnier.

170
00:12:57,939 --> 00:13:00,533
I'm just saying,
if you go to the University of Alaska,

171
00:13:00,609 --> 00:13:02,634
I'm never gonna see you.

172
00:13:07,282 --> 00:13:09,182
They have a really great science program.

173
00:13:10,352 --> 00:13:11,910
You mean, Edward program?

174
00:13:15,023 --> 00:13:17,048
The way he watches you,

175
00:13:17,459 --> 00:13:21,088
it's like he's willing to leap in front
of you and take a bullet or something.

176
00:13:21,730 --> 00:13:23,527
Is that a bad thing?

177
00:13:24,232 --> 00:13:25,597
It's an intense thing.

178
00:13:26,768 --> 00:13:28,827
You're different with him.

179
00:13:29,805 --> 00:13:31,398
He moves, you move.

180
00:13:31,974 --> 00:13:33,566
Like magnets.

181
00:13:34,944 --> 00:13:36,775
I don't know, we're just...

182
00:13:37,346 --> 00:13:39,712
RENEE: In love. I get it.

183
00:13:41,050 --> 00:13:45,009
I just want to make sure
you're making the right choices for you.

184
00:13:45,321 --> 00:13:48,001
You know, 'cause you're the one
that's gonna have to live with them.

185
00:13:51,761 --> 00:13:54,423
All right, enough with the heavy.

186
00:14:01,504 --> 00:14:02,596
Mom.

187
00:14:02,672 --> 00:14:04,503
Congraduation.

188
00:14:04,574 --> 00:14:06,337
I didn't want you
to spend any of your money.

189
00:14:06,409 --> 00:14:08,172
I didn't, come on.

190
00:14:20,124 --> 00:14:21,124
(BOTH LAUGHING)

191
00:14:21,658 --> 00:14:23,853
Are these all our old trip T-shirts?
Mmm-hmm.

192
00:14:23,927 --> 00:14:26,327
BELLA: Get out!
I saved them all.

193
00:14:26,396 --> 00:14:29,422
I thought they'd make a good quilt,
keep you warm up in Alaska.

194
00:14:31,034 --> 00:14:33,468
Remember this one? Ensenada.

195
00:14:34,138 --> 00:14:36,106
The Snake Pit.
Yeah.

196
00:14:36,874 --> 00:14:39,536
But this one is my favorite, here.

197
00:14:39,610 --> 00:14:41,669
The three-headed lobster from Maine.

198
00:14:42,012 --> 00:14:44,742
This is amazing.
Honey, I'm glad you like it.

199
00:14:44,815 --> 00:14:46,305
I just figured, you know,
when you get older,

200
00:14:46,383 --> 00:14:47,680
have kids, we can add to it.

201
00:14:47,751 --> 00:14:50,618
Maybe go visit the world's largest
ketchup bottle or something.

202
00:14:50,687 --> 00:14:51,984
Thanks.

203
00:14:54,525 --> 00:14:56,390
I'm glad you like it.

204
00:14:56,927 --> 00:15:00,363
Just thought you should have
a little piece of me up there in Alaska.

205
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:04,764
Mom...
Yeah?

206
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,007
I miss you.

207
00:15:10,508 --> 00:15:12,976
Honey, I miss you, too.

208
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:33,096
Are you sure this is where you saw her?

209
00:15:34,265 --> 00:15:36,028
She's almost here.

210
00:15:49,047 --> 00:15:50,047
On your left!

211
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:12,831
(GRUNTING)

212
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:27,243
Wait!

213
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:28,816
She's in their territory.

214
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:31,951
She'll get away!

215
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,217
No, she won't!

216
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:11,888
ESME: Emmett, no!

217
00:17:14,734 --> 00:17:15,962
(GRUNTING)

218
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:19,637
(GROWLING)

219
00:17:45,566 --> 00:17:46,692
Do you regret going?

220
00:17:48,903 --> 00:17:49,961
No.

221
00:17:51,639 --> 00:17:53,903
It was really great seeing my mom.

222
00:17:54,308 --> 00:17:56,742
Just really hard saying goodbye.

223
00:17:57,078 --> 00:17:59,205
It doesn't have to be goodbye.

224
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,407
Is that why you asked me to go?

225
00:18:01,549 --> 00:18:04,382
You thought I was gonna change my mind?

226
00:18:05,086 --> 00:18:07,281
I'm always hoping for that.

227
00:18:08,889 --> 00:18:10,083
What?

228
00:18:11,592 --> 00:18:14,425
If I asked you to stay
in the car, would you?

229
00:18:20,735 --> 00:18:22,100
Of course not.

230
00:18:34,616 --> 00:18:35,810
Hey.

231
00:18:37,018 --> 00:18:38,417
Charlie said you left town.

232
00:18:38,653 --> 00:18:40,883
Yeah. To visit my mom. Why?

233
00:18:41,857 --> 00:18:44,587
He's checking to see if you're still human.

234
00:18:45,527 --> 00:18:46,789
Look, I'm here to warn you.

235
00:18:47,996 --> 00:18:49,657
If your kind come on our land again...

236
00:18:50,432 --> 00:18:51,456
Wait, what?

237
00:18:54,302 --> 00:18:55,326
You didn't tell her?

238
00:18:55,737 --> 00:18:56,931
Just leave it alone, Jacob.

239
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,040
Tell me what?

240
00:19:01,143 --> 00:19:04,112
Emmett and Paul had a misunderstanding.

241
00:19:04,379 --> 00:19:06,142
It's nothing to worry about.

242
00:19:06,214 --> 00:19:07,545
JACOB: Listen to you.

243
00:19:08,049 --> 00:19:09,744
Did you lie to get her out of town, too?

244
00:19:09,818 --> 00:19:11,547
You should just leave.

245
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,145
Now.

246
00:19:13,956 --> 00:19:16,049
She has a right to know.

247
00:19:16,726 --> 00:19:18,284
She is the one the redhead wants.

248
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:21,488
Victoria?

249
00:19:23,299 --> 00:19:24,926
Alice's vision.

250
00:19:25,968 --> 00:19:27,993
I was trying to protect you.

251
00:19:28,337 --> 00:19:29,998
By lying to me.

252
00:19:33,109 --> 00:19:35,771
Okay, we're gonna talk about this, but...

253
00:19:35,845 --> 00:19:36,971
You.

254
00:19:37,647 --> 00:19:40,013
Why haven't you called me back?

255
00:19:42,585 --> 00:19:44,519
I had nothing to say.

256
00:19:46,789 --> 00:19:49,280
Well, I have tons. Hold on.
Hey.

257
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:52,591
Bella.

258
00:19:52,962 --> 00:19:54,589
Edward, you have to trust me.

259
00:19:54,664 --> 00:19:56,256
I do trust you.

260
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,298
It's him I don't trust.

261
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:12,913
Hey, lose the grin, Jacob.
We're just going for a ride.

262
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:14,007
Hold on tight.

263
00:20:17,154 --> 00:20:18,985
