00:20:19,089 --> 00:20:22,149
♪ Last born of the clan ♪

265
00:20:22,226 --> 00:20:25,354
♪ First one to be free ♪

266
00:20:25,429 --> 00:20:28,421
♪ Lived inside a house ♪

267
00:20:28,499 --> 00:20:30,660
Are you sure this is a good idea?

268
00:20:32,736 --> 00:20:34,704
I am the vampire girl, remember?

269
00:20:35,873 --> 00:20:37,272
Hey, look who's back!

270
00:20:37,508 --> 00:20:38,508
What up, Bella?

271
00:20:38,575 --> 00:20:40,236
Quil? You, too?
Yep.

272
00:20:40,577 --> 00:20:41,737
Finally made the pack.

273
00:20:42,312 --> 00:20:43,336
EMBRY: I'm glad you're here, Bella.

274
00:20:43,413 --> 00:20:46,075
Maybe we can get a break
from Jake's obsessive inner monologue.

275
00:20:46,149 --> 00:20:47,241
"I wish Bella would call."

276
00:20:47,718 --> 00:20:49,049
"I wish Bella wouldn't call."

277
00:20:49,119 --> 00:20:51,918
"Maybe I should call Bella."
"Maybe I should call Bella and hang up."

278
00:20:51,990 --> 00:20:53,184
(ALL LAUGHING)

279
00:20:53,258 --> 00:20:55,385
All right, you can shut up now.

280
00:20:58,263 --> 00:21:01,790
Bella, this is Leah Clearwater,
Harry's daughter.

281
00:21:02,367 --> 00:21:05,393
Hey. I'm really sorry about your father.

282
00:21:05,837 --> 00:21:08,277
If you're here to torture Jacob some more,
feel free to leave.

283
00:21:11,976 --> 00:21:13,102
Fun, isn't she?

284
00:21:14,345 --> 00:21:16,939
Bella, hi!
Hey.

285
00:21:17,248 --> 00:21:20,115
I was wondering
when we'd see your face around here again.

286
00:21:20,184 --> 00:21:21,549
BELLA: Yeah. Same here.

287
00:21:21,719 --> 00:21:22,719
Sam, we good?

288
00:21:23,354 --> 00:21:26,448
We're good. She won't be getting
through our line any time soon.

289
00:21:26,524 --> 00:21:28,515
Cool.
Yeah, that's right boys!

290
00:21:37,802 --> 00:21:40,135
So when did Leah join the pack?

291
00:21:40,606 --> 00:21:44,269
Around when her dad died.
Her brother, Seth, also phased.

292
00:21:45,110 --> 00:21:48,375
He's only 15,
one of the youngest we've had.

293
00:21:49,248 --> 00:21:52,581
Sam keeps him home studying,
but he's chomping at the bit.

294
00:21:53,385 --> 00:21:55,182
I wish it was Leah who'd stay home.

295
00:21:56,388 --> 00:21:58,583
Come on, don't be such a guy.

296
00:21:58,657 --> 00:22:01,125
No, it's not a chick thing.

297
00:22:01,527 --> 00:22:04,291
It's, you know, a triangle thing.

298
00:22:04,930 --> 00:22:08,525
We all have to live
the Leah Sam Emily pain-fest.

299
00:22:09,969 --> 00:22:11,300
Wolf telepathy, remember?

300
00:22:12,004 --> 00:22:14,131
So Sam dumps Leah for Emily?

301
00:22:14,807 --> 00:22:18,675
Yeah, it wasn't like that.
Sam hates himself for hurting Leah.

302
00:22:19,979 --> 00:22:22,004
But Emily was the one.

303
00:22:23,315 --> 00:22:26,113
I guess it sort of chooses you sometimes.

304
00:22:28,154 --> 00:22:30,088
It's more than some crush, Bella.

305
00:22:30,156 --> 00:22:32,317
Sam imprinted on Emily.

306
00:22:34,227 --> 00:22:36,422
Do I even want to know what that is?

307
00:22:45,605 --> 00:22:48,267
Imprinting on someone is like...

308
00:22:50,644 --> 00:22:52,703
Like when you see her,

309
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,777
everything changes.

310
00:22:57,283 --> 00:23:01,083
All of a sudden,
it's not gravity holding you to the planet.

311
00:23:02,188 --> 00:23:03,485
It's her.

312
00:23:04,391 --> 00:23:06,256
Nothing else matters.

313
00:23:07,494 --> 00:23:09,519
You would do anything,

314
00:23:11,131 --> 00:23:12,860
be anything for her.

315
00:23:15,869 --> 00:23:18,134
Sounds like you know the feeling.

316
00:23:21,976 --> 00:23:23,307
Have you

317
00:23:25,413 --> 00:23:27,381
imprinted on someone?

318
00:23:32,486 --> 00:23:33,976
You'd know if I had.

319
00:23:38,159 --> 00:23:41,185
I just have a direct
line to Sam's thoughts.

320
00:23:42,997 --> 00:23:44,726
So for now you're

321
00:23:45,266 --> 00:23:46,528
still you.

322
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:51,195
And you're still you.

323
00:23:52,373 --> 00:23:53,533
Yeah.

324
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,377
Until graduation.

325
00:24:02,183 --> 00:24:03,514
Graduation?

326
00:24:05,152 --> 00:24:06,882
You knew this was gonna happen.

327
00:24:06,955 --> 00:24:08,047
Not in a month!

328
00:24:10,559 --> 00:24:14,495
I mean, not before you've...
You've even lived.

329
00:24:15,964 --> 00:24:17,556
Or before I could...

330
00:24:17,999 --> 00:24:18,999
(CRASHING)

331
00:24:21,470 --> 00:24:25,201
For a second, just a second, I thought...

332
00:24:27,209 --> 00:24:29,439
But he's got his hooks in you so deep...

333
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:32,910
I decided this, not him.

334
00:24:32,981 --> 00:24:35,347
Bella, they're not even alive.

335
00:24:36,351 --> 00:24:37,909
It makes me sick.

336
00:24:40,589 --> 00:24:43,387
Better you really be dead than one of them.

337
00:24:56,706 --> 00:24:58,139
I can't believe you said that.

338
00:25:02,812 --> 00:25:05,042
Edward was right, I shouldn't have come.

339
00:25:05,114 --> 00:25:08,015
Bella, come on. Please.

340
00:25:11,154 --> 00:25:12,348
I'm sorry.

341
00:26:22,092 --> 00:26:26,392
You know, Edward could
at least respect meal times.

342
00:26:27,197 --> 00:26:28,459
I was just with Jake.

343
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,333
Oh.

344
00:26:31,602 --> 00:26:32,900
Good.

345
00:26:33,171 --> 00:26:34,263
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

346
00:26:37,508 --> 00:26:40,841
I'll just give you two some privacy, then.

347
00:26:43,181 --> 00:26:45,149
Hey.
Do you understand how worried I've been?

348
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:46,983
I was perfectly safe.

349
00:26:47,051 --> 00:26:49,212
I almost broke the treaty to make sure.

350
00:26:50,288 --> 00:26:53,382
I know I smell like a dog. I'm sorry.
No, something's wrong.

351
00:27:00,565 --> 00:27:02,226
Edward, what's wrong?

352
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:04,291
Someone's been in here.

353
00:27:09,474 --> 00:27:11,965
DR. CULLEN: Who was it?
Someone we know?

354
00:27:12,911 --> 00:27:16,005
This stranger, I didn't
recognize his scent.

355
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,741
A nomad passing through?

356
00:27:17,815 --> 00:27:19,815
A passerby wouldn't
have left Bella's father alive.

357
00:27:20,285 --> 00:27:24,188
The scent disappeared
about 5 miles south of Bella's house.

358
00:27:25,057 --> 00:27:26,957
Someone's orchestrating this.

359
00:27:27,026 --> 00:27:28,391
Victoria?

360
00:27:29,061 --> 00:27:30,619
I would have seen her decide.

361
00:27:30,863 --> 00:27:31,955
Has to be the Volturi.

362
00:27:32,665 --> 00:27:35,293
I don't think it's the Volturi, either.

363
00:27:35,367 --> 00:27:37,130
I've been watching Aro's decisions, too.

364
00:27:37,202 --> 00:27:38,533
EMMETT: So we keep looking.

365
00:27:38,604 --> 00:27:41,038
We'll also take shifts
guarding Bella at her house.

366
00:27:41,540 --> 00:27:42,939
Another protection detail?

367
00:27:43,442 --> 00:27:44,739
DR. CULLEN: Rosalie.

368
00:27:45,811 --> 00:27:46,811
No, she's right.

369
00:27:47,279 --> 00:27:51,716
You can't protect me, watch my dad
and search for the intruder.

370
00:27:51,784 --> 00:27:53,547
And for Victoria.

371
00:27:53,619 --> 00:27:55,280
And keep yourselves fed.

372
00:27:55,354 --> 00:27:57,151
I'm not leaving you here defenseless.

373
00:27:57,222 --> 00:27:59,782
Well, I'm not gonna let you starve.

374
00:28:00,259 --> 00:28:02,250
And I wouldn't be unprotected. I have...

375
00:28:04,263 --> 00:28:05,491
EDWARD: What?

376
00:28:13,373 --> 00:28:15,603
Whoever it was, he left his stink behind.

377
00:28:16,309 --> 00:28:20,040
It'll be hard to miss when we cross
it again. We'll handle it from here.

378
00:28:20,246 --> 00:28:22,908
We don't need you to handle anything.

379
00:28:22,983 --> 00:28:24,075
Or anyone.

380
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:25,811
I could care less what you need.

381
00:28:25,885 --> 00:28:27,819
All right, we're done here.

382
00:28:27,887 --> 00:28:29,855
No, you're done here.
BELLA: Stop!

383
00:28:30,690 --> 00:28:34,182
I'm tired of this.
From now on, I'm Switzerland, okay?

384
00:28:35,528 --> 00:28:37,462
BELLA: Edward hated the idea,

385
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:40,226
but it wasn't about rivalry anymore.

386
00:28:40,934 --> 00:28:43,664
It was about my safety, and Charlie's.

387
00:28:44,738 --> 00:28:49,175
In the days that followed, I got them
to at least try to work together.

388
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:57,277
The wolves took over
so the Cullens could hunt.

389
00:28:59,754 --> 00:29:02,348
It wasn't exactly an easy alliance.

390
00:29:03,324 --> 00:29:04,382
(GROWLS)

391
00:29:18,706 --> 00:29:19,968
Doesn't he own a shirt?

392
00:29:25,212 --> 00:29:26,509
I'm good here. You should go.

393
00:29:27,281 --> 00:29:29,408
I'm not gonna be gone long.

394
00:29:29,483 --> 00:29:32,043
Don't rush. You need to hunt.

395
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:50,704
Maybe rush a little bit.

396
00:29:56,344 --> 00:29:58,141
Hey, beautiful.
Hi.

397
00:30:03,819 --> 00:30:05,480
(TIRES SCREECHING)

398
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:10,820
So, what do you wanna do today?

399
00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:13,884
Bike, hike, just hang? Your call.

400
00:30:14,396 --> 00:30:16,296
But we're going to a party tonight.

401
00:30:19,167 --> 00:30:21,032
Are you sure this is okay?

402
00:30:21,636 --> 00:30:23,934
I really hate being a party crasher.

403
00:30:24,339 --> 00:30:27,035
Technically,
you're a council meeting crasher.

404
00:30:27,776 --> 00:30:32,440
You see? The council leaders,
Dad, Quil's grandpa and Sue Clearwater.

405
00:30:33,415 --> 00:30:35,406
She took over for Harry when he died.

406
00:30:35,484 --> 00:30:37,282
Okay, I should not be here.

407
00:30:37,954 --> 00:30:40,479
You're okay. I thought...

408
00:30:41,591 --> 00:30:45,288
I mean, they thought it would
be good for you to hear the histories.

409
00:30:45,361 --> 00:30:46,919
The histories?

410
00:30:47,497 --> 00:30:50,398
The tribe's histories? Aren't they secret?

411
00:30:51,234 --> 00:30:54,863
We all got a role to play,
and you're part of this.

412
00:30:55,671 --> 00:30:58,697
I mean, it's the first time
Seth, Leah and Quil'll hear them, too.

413
00:30:58,774 --> 00:31:01,937
But you are the first outsider. Ever.

414
00:31:04,347 --> 00:31:07,248
If I had known that, I would have, like...

415
00:31:08,151 --> 00:31:10,551
I don't know, dressed better.
SETH: Jake!

416
00:31:11,821 --> 00:31:14,813
Hey.
It's about time you got here.

417
00:31:14,891 --> 00:31:17,917
Paul's been hoovering the grub,
but I saved you some burgers.

418
00:31:17,994 --> 00:31:19,825
Good looking out, bro.

419
00:31:20,096 --> 00:31:23,031
Bella, this is Seth Clearwater,
Leah's brother.

420
00:31:23,099 --> 00:31:24,430
Hi.
Newest member of the pack.

421
00:31:25,168 --> 00:31:27,262
Newest. Bestest. Brightest.

422
00:31:27,337 --> 00:31:28,827
And slowest.

423
00:31:31,542 --> 00:31:34,443
Come on, your dad's about to start.
Okay.

424
00:31:35,846 --> 00:31:39,509
The Quileutes have been a small tribe
from the beginning,

425
00:31:40,150 --> 00:31:43,176
but we have always had magic in our blood.

426
00:31:44,888 --> 00:31:46,617
We were great spirit warriors,

427
00:31:47,257 --> 00:31:51,785
shape-shifters that transformed
to the powerful wolf.

428
00:31:53,730 --> 00:31:57,222
This enabled us to scare off our enemies

429
00:31:57,467 --> 00:31:59,560
and protect our tribe.

430
00:32:01,605 --> 00:32:06,167
One day,
our warriors came across a creature.

431
00:32:07,678 --> 00:32:09,703
It looked like a man,

432
00:32:09,780 --> 00:32:11,975
but it was hard like stone

433
00:32:12,749 --> 00:32:14,615
and cold as ice.

434
00:32:20,625 --> 00:32:22,092
(GRUNTING)

435
00:32:28,566 --> 00:32:29,999
(GROWLING)

436
00:32:34,806 --> 00:32:38,867
Our warriors' sharp teeth
finally tore it apart,

437
00:32:38,943 --> 00:32:42,140
but only fire would completely destroy it.

438
00:32:43,548 --> 00:32:46,881
They lived in fear
that the cold man was not alone.

439
00:32:48,586 --> 00:32:49,951
And they were right.

440
00:32:50,154 --> 00:32:51,451
(SCREAMING)

441
00:32:51,856 --> 00:32:53,153
(ALL CLAMORING)

442
00:32:54,325 --> 00:32:57,294
She took her vengeance out on the village.

443
00:32:59,931 --> 00:33:02,263
Our elder chief, Taha Aki,

444
00:33:02,333 --> 00:33:07,431
was the only spirit warrior left
to save the tribe after his son was killed.

445
00:33:08,774 --> 00:33:10,002
(CRYING)

446
00:33:12,177 --> 00:33:13,177
(YELLING)

447
00:33:19,785 --> 00:33:23,277
Taha Aki's third wife
could see that he would lose.

448
00:33:24,556 --> 00:33:27,855
The third wife was no magical being,

449
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,790
with no special powers but one,

450
00:33:32,831 --> 00:33:34,059
courage.

451
00:33:34,199 --> 00:33:35,199
(SCREAMING)

452
00:33:45,644 --> 00:33:48,807
The third wife's sacrifice
distracted the cold woman

453
00:33:48,881 --> 00:33:51,475
long enough for Taha Aki to destroy her.

454
00:33:53,053 --> 00:33:55,317
She saved the tribe.

455
00:33:55,822 --> 00:33:58,916
Over time, our enemies have disappeared.

456
00:34:00,093 --> 00:34:01,890
But one remains,

457
00:34:03,396 --> 00:34:04,886
the cold ones.

458
00:34:07,834 --> 00:34:10,132
Our magic awakens when they're near,

459
00:34:10,403 --> 00:34:12,268
and we sense it now.

460
00:34:12,339 --> 00:34:13,772
We feel the threat in our blood.

461
00:34:16,176 --> 00:34:18,303
Something terrible is coming,

462
00:34:20,347 --> 00:34:22,713
and we must all be ready,

463
00:34:23,683 --> 00:34:24,980
all of us.

464
00:34:29,689 --> 00:34:30,849
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

465
00:34:39,466 --> 00:34:40,466
(GRUNTS)

466
00:34:45,306 --> 00:34:46,637
(GASPING)

467
00:34:52,279 --> 00:34:54,270
What did you do to me?

468
00:34:58,352 --> 00:34:59,876
I'm so...

469
00:34:59,954 --> 00:35:02,184
Yeah. I know.

470
00:35:03,824 --> 00:35:05,104
We'll find you someone to drink.

471
00:35:05,559 --> 00:35:06,559
MALE VAMPIRE: Mine!

472
00:35:13,901 --> 00:35:16,597
Just try not to get killed, will you?

473
00:35:20,007 --> 00:35:22,066
I'm gonna need numbers.

474
00:35:23,444 --> 00:35:25,674
Seattle is in a state of terror.

475
00:35:25,746 --> 00:35:29,614
Police are baffled by
the escalating murders and disappearances.

476
00:35:29,684 --> 00:35:33,586
Theories range from a vicious new gang
to a wildly active serial killer.

477
00:35:33,655 --> 00:35:34,679
Reporting live...

478
00:35:34,756 --> 00:35:38,055
It's getting worse.
We're going to have to do something.

479
00:35:38,794 --> 00:35:42,560
It takes more than one of our kind
to cause the damage they're reporting.

480
00:35:42,831 --> 00:35:46,790
Quite a few more.
And they're undisciplined, conspicuous.

481
00:35:46,868 --> 00:35:48,233
It's newborns.

482
00:35:49,938 --> 00:35:51,769
What, like new vampires?

483
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:53,865
In the first few months after the change.

484
00:35:53,942 --> 00:35:57,537
That's when
we're at our most uncontrollable. Vicious.

485
00:35:58,313 --> 00:36:00,076
Insane with thirst.

486
00:36:00,615 --> 00:36:02,879
Something to look forward to.

487
00:36:04,753 --> 00:36:07,813
No one's trained these newborns,
but this isn't random.

488
00:36:08,824 --> 00:36:10,815
Someone's creating an army.

489
00:36:11,193 --> 00:36:13,286
Well, now we're definitely
going to Seattle.

490
00:36:14,362 --> 00:36:16,057
An army of vampires?

491
00:36:16,131 --> 00:36:18,122
And they've been created to fight someone.

492
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,896
We're the only clan even close to Seattle.

493
00:36:19,969 --> 00:36:21,436
DR. CULLEN: Regardless of why
they were made,

494
00:36:21,504 --> 00:36:24,632
if we don't put a stop to them,
the Volturi will.

495
00:36:24,707 --> 00:36:26,766
I'm surprised they've
let it go on this long.

496
00:36:26,843 --> 00:36:28,276
Maybe they're behind it.

497
00:36:29,545 --> 00:36:32,241
In Italy, I read Aro's mind.

498
00:36:32,315 --> 00:36:34,078
He wants me and Alice to join him,

499
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:37,313
but he knows we'll never choose him
as long as our family's still alive.

500
00:36:37,386 --> 00:36:40,048
An army could solve that for him.

501
00:36:48,698 --> 00:36:49,858
Hey.

502
00:36:50,733 --> 00:36:52,530
Did you eat dinner yet?

503
00:36:54,437 --> 00:36:56,132
No, I haven't.

504
00:36:57,106 --> 00:36:58,334
(CHARLIE SIGHS)

505
00:36:59,475 --> 00:37:03,741
This kid, Riley Biers,
disappeared over a year ago,

506
00:37:04,847 --> 00:37:08,409
and his poor parents have been papering
Seattle with these things ever since.

507
00:37:10,454 --> 00:37:11,978
You think they should just give up?

508
00:37:14,992 --> 00:37:17,620
Well, I wouldn't if it were you.

509
00:37:20,063 --> 00:37:21,462
Not ever.

510
00:37:27,804 --> 00:37:29,704
BELLA: I have to figure out
what to tell people.

511
00:37:30,874 --> 00:37:33,536
Why I won't be home for Christmases,

512
00:37:34,177 --> 00:37:36,372
and why I won't visit,

513
00:37:38,015 --> 00:37:40,540
why they'll never see me again.

514
00:37:40,784 --> 00:37:44,618
After a few decades,
everyone you know will be dead.

515
00:37:47,357 --> 00:37:48,688
Problem solved.

516
00:37:53,897 --> 00:37:56,389
Why are you so against
me becoming like you?

517
00:37:56,935 --> 00:37:58,527
I've told you.

518
00:38:01,606 --> 00:38:03,335
Be honest with me.

519
00:38:04,642 --> 00:38:06,109
There's more.

520
00:38:06,578 --> 00:38:11,038
I know the consequences
of this choice you're making.

521
00:38:16,287 --> 00:38:17,686
I've lived through it.

522
00:38:19,557 --> 00:38:22,185
And to let you suffer that...

523
00:38:23,728 --> 00:38:27,323
You believe I have a soul, and I don't.

524
00:38:30,835 --> 00:38:32,427
But to risk yours,

525
00:38:32,503 --> 00:38:35,597
just for the sake of
never having to lose you,

526
00:38:37,909 --> 00:38:40,173
that's the most selfish thing I'll ever do.

527
00:38:44,582 --> 00:38:48,576
I thought that you were afraid
that I'd be too different.

528
00:38:50,756 --> 00:38:55,955
You know, like, I wouldn't be warm,
and I wouldn't smell the same.

529
00:39:05,704 --> 00:39:07,331
You'll always be my Bella.

530
00:39:29,094 --> 00:39:31,585
My Bella, just less fragile.

531
00:39:42,575 --> 00:39:44,668
BELLA: Gosh, it's so pretty here.

532
00:39:50,250 --> 00:39:53,310
So, Alice has planned
a big graduation party.

533
00:39:54,454 --> 00:39:55,546
Which you're invited to.

534
00:40:00,260 --> 00:40:02,922
Yeah, I figured that.

535
00:40:10,670 --> 00:40:11,830
What?

536
00:40:13,807 --> 00:40:16,332
I just wanted to do this differently.

537
00:40:16,743 --> 00:40:18,074
Smoother.

538
00:40:19,646 --> 00:40:21,580
But now I'm out of time.

539
00:40:22,917 --> 00:40:24,214
Do what?

540
00:40:25,086 --> 00:40:27,714
You need to hear the truth, Bella,

541
00:40:28,355 --> 00:40:30,687
understand all your options.

542
00:40:32,259 --> 00:40:34,022
And you need to know

543
00:40:35,596 --> 00:40:37,826
that I'm in love with you,

544
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:42,326
and I want you to choose me
instead of him.

545
00:40:44,371 --> 00:40:46,566
I thought you understood.

546
00:40:49,410 --> 00:40:51,878
I don't feel that way for you.
I don't buy it.

547
00:40:51,946 --> 00:40:53,846
What don't you buy?

548
00:40:55,349 --> 00:40:56,646
That's how I feel.

549
00:40:57,418 --> 00:41:00,979
You feel something else for me.
You just won't admit it.

550
00:41:02,323 --> 00:41:04,291
So I'm not giving up.

551
00:41:05,092 --> 00:41:07,219
I'm gonna fight for you

552
00:41:10,097 --> 00:41:12,726
until your heart stops beating.

553
00:41:13,101 --> 00:41:14,830
Well, then you're not gonna
have to fight for long.

554
00:41:14,903 --> 00:41:17,201
You're rushing into it because
you're afraid you'll change your mind.

555
00:41:17,272 --> 00:41:18,864
No, I'm not.

556
00:41:20,275 --> 00:41:22,072
I know what I want.

557
00:41:23,512 --> 00:41:26,538
You wouldn't have to change for me, Bella,

558
00:41:27,249 --> 00:41:29,444
or say goodbye to anybody.

559
00:41:30,519 --> 00:41:33,079
I can give you more than him.

560
00:41:34,089 --> 00:41:38,321
I mean, he probably can't even kiss you
without hurting you.

561
00:41:39,761 --> 00:41:41,126
Feel that?

562
00:41:42,130 --> 00:41:44,360
Flesh and blood.

563
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,729
And warmth.

564
00:41:57,445 --> 00:41:58,469
(GRUNTS)

565
00:41:58,547 --> 00:41:59,673
God!

566
00:42:01,350 --> 00:42:02,578
God!

567
00:42:10,426 --> 00:42:11,450
Edward!

568
00:42:11,527 --> 00:42:13,791
If you ever touch her
against her will again...

569
00:42:13,863 --> 00:42:15,854
Don't do this here!
She's not sure what she wants.

570
00:42:15,932 --> 00:42:17,365
Don't do this here!
Let me give you a clue.

571
00:42:17,433 --> 00:42:18,832
Wait for her to say the words.

572
00:42:18,901 --> 00:42:21,165
Fine! And she will.

573
00:42:21,537 --> 00:42:22,936
Jacob, just go, okay?

574
00:42:23,005 --> 00:42:25,735
CHARLIE: Hey, hey, hey! Easy, guys. Easy.

575
00:42:26,142 --> 00:42:28,804
Let's take it down a notch. All right?

576
00:42:32,048 --> 00:42:33,140
What's going on?

577
00:42:37,053 --> 00:42:38,053
I kissed Bella.

578
00:42:42,658 --> 00:42:44,091
And she broke her hand.

579
00:42:46,362 --> 00:42:47,556
Punching my face.

580
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,165
Total misunderstanding.

581
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:55,203
DR. CULLEN: It's just a sprain.

582
00:42:55,372 --> 00:42:57,533
It should heal fairly quickly.

583
00:42:59,042 --> 00:43:02,478
Trying to walk and chew gum
at the same time again, Bella?

584
00:43:03,313 --> 00:43:04,803
I punched a werewolf in the face.

585
00:43:04,982 --> 00:43:08,577
Bad ass.
You're gonna be one tough little newborn.

586
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:11,483
Tough enough to take you on.

587
00:43:17,794 --> 00:43:19,227
Don't worry about it.

588
00:43:22,499 --> 00:43:24,091
Got any leads?

589
00:43:24,468 --> 00:43:28,802
No sign of the intruder. But Victoria
continues to make appearances.

590
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:38,906
Go blather to someone else
about the joys of becoming a newborn.

591
00:43:43,454 --> 00:43:44,682
Okay...

592
00:43:45,757 --> 00:43:47,190
Rosalie,

593
00:43:49,327 --> 00:43:52,023
I don't understand what I did
to make you hate me so much.

594
00:43:52,363 --> 00:43:53,421
Hate...

595
00:43:55,500 --> 00:43:56,660
I don't hate you.

596
00:43:59,837 --> 00:44:02,704
I don't particularly like you, but...

597
00:44:07,278 --> 00:44:09,371
Bella, I envy you.

598
00:44:10,381 --> 00:44:11,643
What?

599
00:44:12,951 --> 00:44:15,249
That's ridiculous.
No, it's not.

600
00:44:17,488 --> 00:44:18,955
You have a choice.

601
00:44:19,223 --> 00:44:20,690
I didn't.

602
00:44:21,626 --> 00:44:25,255
None of us did.
But you do, and you're choosing wrong.

603
00:44:26,364 --> 00:44:29,266
I don't care
how miserable your human life is.

604
00:44:30,135 --> 00:44:32,763
My life is not miserable.

605
00:44:35,941 --> 00:44:39,206
I mean, it's not perfect.
Nobody's life is perfect.

606
00:44:39,678 --> 00:44:41,077
Mine was.

607
00:44:41,780 --> 00:44:43,680
Absolutely perfect.

608
00:44:45,451 --> 00:44:47,316
There were things I still wanted,

609
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:50,010
to be married, with a nice house

610
00:44:50,089 --> 00:44:52,284
and a husband to kiss me
when he came home,

611
00:44:52,725 --> 00:44:54,784
a family of my own.

612
00:44:55,728 --> 00:44:59,095
Royce King was the most eligible bachelor
in town.

613
00:45:00,165 --> 00:45:02,030
I barely knew him.

614
00:45:06,305 --> 00:45:10,264
But I was young.
I was in love with the idea of love.

615
00:45:11,844 --> 00:45:15,302
On the last night of my life,
I left a friend's house late.

616
00:45:15,381 --> 00:45:16,872
I wasn't far from home.

617
00:45:16,950 --> 00:45:18,645
There she is.

618
00:45:18,718 --> 00:45:19,742
Hey, Rose!

619
00:45:20,754 --> 00:45:23,120
Come over here! Here. Hold this.

620
00:45:23,990 --> 00:45:25,651
Hey, come over here.

621
00:45:26,126 --> 00:45:28,424
We've been waiting for you.

622
00:45:29,329 --> 00:45:30,990
There she is.

623
00:45:32,399 --> 00:45:34,094
Royce. Royce!

624
00:45:34,167 --> 00:45:35,464
(MEN LAUGHING)

625
00:45:35,535 --> 00:45:37,298
You're drunk.

626
00:45:37,370 --> 00:45:40,862
Isn't she lovely, John?
I told you she was a looker.

627
00:45:40,940 --> 00:45:43,465
It's hard to say with all those clothes on.

628
00:45:43,877 --> 00:45:45,071
What do you say, Rose?

629
00:45:45,645 --> 00:45:47,885
Why don't we take off a few layers?
Stop it, stop it.

630
00:45:48,048 --> 00:45:50,016
Stop. Stop!

631
00:45:52,519 --> 00:45:53,850
I'll see you tomorrow.

632
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,251
Sober.

633
00:45:56,790 --> 00:45:58,155
Hey, where do you think you're going?

634
00:45:58,224 --> 00:46:00,624
I said, get... Come back... Hey!
Stop! Stop! Get off me!

635
00:46:00,693 --> 00:46:02,661
You'll do as I say!
Let go of me! Stop!

636
00:46:02,729 --> 00:46:05,062
Stop! Let go! Stop!

637
00:46:07,768 --> 00:46:10,794
They left me in the street,
thinking I was dead.

638
00:46:11,205 --> 00:46:13,105
Believe me, I wanted to be.

639
00:46:14,809 --> 00:46:16,936
Carlisle found me. He
smelled all the blood.

640
00:46:17,411 --> 00:46:20,209
Thought he was helping me.
I'm sorry.

641
00:46:22,983 --> 00:46:25,281
I got my revenge on them.

642
00:46:26,787 --> 00:46:28,448
One at a time.

643
00:46:28,856 --> 00:46:31,620
Saved Royce for last,
so he'd know I was coming.

644
00:46:33,427 --> 00:46:34,427
(BANGING ON DOOR)

645
00:46:35,396 --> 00:46:36,556
(SCREAMS)

646
00:46:50,211 --> 00:46:52,577
I was a little theatrical back then.

647
00:47:01,456 --> 00:47:04,357
Things got better after I found Emmett.

648
00:47:06,795 --> 00:47:08,956
But we'll always be this.

649
00:47:12,667 --> 00:47:13,861
Frozen.

650
00:47:15,003 --> 00:47:16,527
Never moving forward.

651
00:47:18,406 --> 00:47:22,001
That's what I miss the most. Possibilities.

652
00:47:23,378 --> 00:47:25,903
Sitting on a front porch somewhere,

653
00:47:26,148 --> 00:47:28,776
Emmett, gray-haired, by my side,

654
00:47:28,850 --> 00:47:31,478
surrounded by our grandchildren.

655
00:47:32,787 --> 00:47:34,516
Their laughter.

656
00:47:36,525 --> 00:47:39,426
I understand that that's what you want.

657
00:47:46,335 --> 00:47:49,236
But there's nothing
I'm ever gonna want more

658
00:47:51,974 --> 00:47:53,566
than Edward.

659
00:47:54,310 --> 00:47:56,244
You're wrong again.

660
00:47:58,080 --> 00:48:01,982
After you've been changed,
there's one thing you'll want more,

661
00:48:02,485 --> 00:48:03,816
one thing you'll kill for.

662
00:48:06,722 --> 00:48:08,087
Blood.

663
00:48:12,461 --> 00:48:13,792
(VAMPIRES SCREAMING)

664
00:48:13,863 --> 00:48:17,026
What did I say about a low profile?

665
00:48:19,368 --> 00:48:20,767
(INDISTINCT SCREAMING)

666
00:48:29,445 --> 00:48:31,345
Something's coming.

667
00:48:33,450 --> 00:48:37,546
Something bigger than any of us alone.

668
00:48:38,989 --> 00:48:43,551
And if you can't control yourselves,

669
00:48:46,363 --> 00:48:48,456
we're all going to die.

670
00:48:52,769 --> 00:48:55,067
What's done is done, just

671
00:48:57,708 --> 00:49:00,040
clean up after yourselves.

672
00:49:08,719 --> 00:49:11,745
They've already drawn too much attention.

673
00:49:11,822 --> 00:49:13,153
So has our inaction.

674
00:49:14,191 --> 00:49:17,854
Others may begin to question
the Volturi's effectiveness.

675
00:49:18,795 --> 00:49:20,262
Let them.

676
00:49:25,803 --> 00:49:27,964
Maybe we should consult with Aro.

677
00:49:30,241 --> 00:49:31,241
(GRUNTS)

678
00:49:33,044 --> 00:49:35,308
Aro's decisions are being watched.

679
00:49:37,382 --> 00:49:39,111
We must decide.

680
00:49:41,552 --> 00:49:44,749
Then decide, sister. It's time.

681
00:49:46,724 --> 00:49:48,487
Yes, it is.

682
00:49:53,398 --> 00:49:56,196
Either we let them do
what they were created for,

683
00:49:57,268 --> 00:49:59,065
or we end them.

684
00:50:00,004 --> 00:50:01,972
Decisions, decisions.

685
00:50:12,484 --> 00:50:16,784
When we were five, they asked us
what we wanted to be when we grew up.

686
00:50:16,855 --> 00:50:20,951
Our answers were things
like astronaut, president,

687
00:50:21,593 --> 00:50:24,289
or, in my case, a princess.
(ALL CHUCKLING)

688
00:50:24,363 --> 00:50:26,991
When we were 10, they asked again.

689
00:50:27,066 --> 00:50:31,935
We answered rock star, cowboy
or, in my case, a gold medalist.

690
00:50:32,938 --> 00:50:36,669
But now that we've grown up,
they want a serious answer.

691
00:50:37,242 --> 00:50:39,233
Well, how about this?

692
00:50:40,012 --> 00:50:41,536
Who the hell knows?

693
00:50:41,647 --> 00:50:42,647
(ALL CHEERING)

694
00:50:42,815 --> 00:50:43,975
Yeah!

695
00:50:45,818 --> 00:50:48,013
This isn't the time to make
hard-and-fast decisions.

696
00:50:48,087 --> 00:50:49,748
This is the time to make mistakes.

697
00:50:50,789 --> 00:50:53,758
Take the wrong train
and get stuck somewhere.

698
00:50:53,826 --> 00:50:56,488
Fall in love a lot.

699
00:50:57,896 --> 00:51:02,095
Major in philosophy, because there's
no way to make a career out of that.

700
00:51:02,168 --> 00:51:06,002
Change your mind, and change it again,
because nothing's permanent.

701
00:51:07,173 --> 00:51:09,733
So make as many mistakes as you can.

702
00:51:10,210 --> 00:51:12,906
That way, someday,
when they ask what we want to be,

703
00:51:13,380 --> 00:51:14,745
we won't have to guess.

704
00:51:16,216 --> 00:51:17,808
We'll know.

705
00:51:17,917 --> 00:51:19,111
(ALL APPLAUDING)

706
00:51:25,392 --> 00:51:26,984
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

707
00:51:45,378 --> 00:51:46,675
You made it!

708
00:51:47,148 --> 00:51:49,639
Hey. What did you think of my speech?

709
00:51:49,717 --> 00:51:52,686
Too easy-breezy? Too self-helpful?
You hated it?

710
00:51:52,753 --> 00:51:55,347
No. I think you pretty much nailed it.
JESSICA: Yeah?

711
00:51:55,656 --> 00:51:57,954
It's like I was born to lead, right?

712
00:51:58,025 --> 00:51:59,788
I love this song! Let's go.

713
00:51:59,960 --> 00:52:01,552
♪ (UPBEAT SONG PLAYING) ♪

714
00:52:24,718 --> 00:52:26,049
What are you doing here?

715
00:52:26,520 --> 00:52:28,385
You invited me, remember?

716
00:52:29,156 --> 00:52:33,092
Was my right hook too subtle for you?
That was me uninviting you.

717
00:52:33,928 --> 00:52:37,490
Look, Bella, I'm sorry about, you know,

718
00:52:39,034 --> 00:52:41,502
the kiss and your hand.

719
00:52:42,404 --> 00:52:46,534
I'd blame it on the whole inner animal
thing, but it was really just me

720
00:52:47,175 --> 00:52:48,870
being an ass.

721
00:52:49,644 --> 00:52:51,077
I'm really sorry.

722
00:52:52,714 --> 00:52:54,545
I brought you something.

723
00:52:54,850 --> 00:52:58,115
A graduation present. I made it myself.

724
00:52:59,020 --> 00:53:00,453
BELLA: Wow.

725
00:53:00,922 --> 00:53:02,219
You made this?

726
00:53:03,191 --> 00:53:04,783
It's really pretty.

727
00:53:05,060 --> 00:53:06,459
Thanks.

728
00:53:21,209 --> 00:53:22,267
I'll be right back.

729
00:53:25,348 --> 00:53:28,545
Alice, what'd you see?
The decision's been made.

730
00:53:28,618 --> 00:53:30,176
What's going on?

731
00:53:30,253 --> 00:53:32,744
You're not going to Seattle.
No.

732
00:53:33,923 --> 00:53:35,823
They're coming here.

733
00:53:36,425 --> 00:53:38,017
ALICE: They'll be here in four days.

734
00:53:38,094 --> 00:53:39,994
This could turn into a bloodbath.

735
00:53:40,162 --> 00:53:41,186
Who's behind it?

736
00:53:41,264 --> 00:53:43,732
I didn't see anyone I recognized.

737
00:53:44,333 --> 00:53:45,333
Maybe one.

738
00:53:46,502 --> 00:53:49,903
I know his face. He's local. Riley Biers.

739
00:53:50,740 --> 00:53:51,764
He didn't start this.

740
00:53:51,841 --> 00:53:53,832
Whoever did is staying out of the action.

741
00:53:54,176 --> 00:53:56,542
They must be playing with the blind spots
in your vision.

742
00:53:56,612 --> 00:53:58,580
JASPER: Either way, the army is coming

743
00:53:58,648 --> 00:54:00,275
and there aren't enough of us
to protect the town.

744
00:54:00,349 --> 00:54:03,250
Hold up. What damn army?

745
00:54:03,319 --> 00:54:05,287
Newborns. Our kind.

746
00:54:05,521 --> 00:54:06,647
What are they after?

747
00:54:06,889 --> 00:54:08,789
They were passing around Bella's scent.

748
00:54:09,191 --> 00:54:10,488
A red blouse.

749
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:13,928
They're after Bella?
What the hell does this mean?

750
00:54:13,997 --> 00:54:16,898
It means an ugly fight. With lives lost.

751
00:54:22,039 --> 00:54:24,234
All right. We're in.

752
00:54:24,675 --> 00:54:27,735
No. You'd get yourselves killed. No way.

753
00:54:28,278 --> 00:54:30,542
I wasn't asking for permission.

754
00:54:31,148 --> 00:54:32,547
Edward?

755
00:54:36,386 --> 00:54:37,876
It means more protection for you.

756
00:54:39,289 --> 00:54:43,953
Jacob, do you believe
Sam would agree to an understanding?

757
00:54:45,696 --> 00:54:48,324
As long as we get to kill some vampires.

758
00:54:48,398 --> 00:54:49,422
DR. CULLEN: Jasper?

759
00:54:49,499 --> 00:54:51,524
They'll give us the numbers.

760
00:54:52,736 --> 00:54:56,729
Newborns won't know they even exist.
That'll give us an edge.

761
00:54:56,807 --> 00:54:58,240
We'll need to coordinate.

762
00:54:58,308 --> 00:55:02,142
Carlisle, they're gonna get hurt.
We'll all need some training.

763
00:55:02,212 --> 00:55:05,182
Fighting newborns requires knowledge
that Jasper has.

764
00:55:05,249 --> 00:55:07,342
You're welcome to join us.

765
00:55:08,686 --> 00:55:11,780
All right. Name the time and place.

766
00:55:11,856 --> 00:55:15,690
Jake, you don't know
what you're getting yourself into.

767
00:55:17,128 --> 00:55:18,493
Bella,

768
00:55:19,097 --> 00:55:20,997
this is what we do.

769
00:55:21,532 --> 00:55:22,863
You should be happy.

770
00:55:23,501 --> 00:55:26,163
Look at us, working together.

771
00:55:26,638 --> 00:55:30,165
You are the one who wanted us
to get along. Remember?

772
00:55:39,717 --> 00:55:40,945
Again!

773
00:55:54,066 --> 00:55:56,261
It's a graduation present.

774
00:56:12,785 --> 00:56:14,082
(GROWLING)

775
00:56:15,421 --> 00:56:18,219
They don't trust us enough
to be in their human forms.

776
00:56:18,290 --> 00:56:20,417
They came. That's what matters.

777
00:56:21,694 --> 00:56:23,457
Will you translate?

778
00:56:28,500 --> 00:56:29,797
Hey, Jake.

779
00:56:35,908 --> 00:56:37,307
Welcome.

780
00:56:39,511 --> 00:56:43,312
Jasper has experience with newborns.
He'll teach us how to defeat them.

781
00:56:46,753 --> 00:56:48,713
They want to know
how the newborns differ from us.

782
00:56:49,923 --> 00:56:51,515
They're a great deal stronger than us

783
00:56:51,591 --> 00:56:54,458
because their own human blood
lingers in their tissues.

784
00:56:55,228 --> 00:56:58,322
Our kind is never more physically powerful

785
00:56:58,798 --> 00:57:00,993
than in our first several
months of this life.

