01:17:52,917 --> 01:17:56,080
It's not modern. It's ancient.

1035
01:17:59,110 --> 01:18:01,169
I'm from a different era.

1036
01:18:03,563 --> 01:18:07,090
Things were a lot less complicated.

1037
01:18:09,365 --> 01:18:13,825
And if I'd have met you back then,
I would have courted you.

1038
01:18:16,102 --> 01:18:21,267
We'd have taken chaperoned strolls
and iced tea on the porch.

1039
01:18:31,967 --> 01:18:34,333
I may have stolen a kiss or two,

1040
01:18:35,461 --> 01:18:40,785
but only after asking
your father's permission.

1041
01:18:42,695 --> 01:18:44,253
I would have got down on one knee,

1042
01:18:51,270 --> 01:18:54,239
and I would have
presented you with a ring.

1043
01:19:01,172 --> 01:19:02,264
This was my mother's.

1044
01:19:06,583 --> 01:19:11,543
Isabella Swan, I promise to love you
every moment of forever.

1045
01:19:12,715 --> 01:19:16,378
And would you do me
the extraordinary honor of marrying me?

1046
01:19:22,367 --> 01:19:23,732
Yes.

1047
01:19:29,843 --> 01:19:33,968
♪ ♪

1048
01:19:45,592 --> 01:19:47,685
You're not coming with us?

1049
01:19:56,206 --> 01:19:58,697
It'll be a last minute decision.

1050
01:20:00,773 --> 01:20:06,006
I told you how it works.
The Cullens have powers.

1051
01:20:07,127 --> 01:20:11,826
Don't underestimate them, Riley.
You'll have the numbers,

1052
01:20:12,745 --> 01:20:17,945
but they'll be able
to anticipate your every move.

1053
01:20:19,399 --> 01:20:22,163
According to your friend?
Yes.

1054
01:20:22,706 --> 01:20:25,573
My dead friend.

1055
01:20:28,368 --> 01:20:31,633
Laurent found out about the things
they could do,

1056
01:20:33,633 --> 01:20:35,464
and they killed him.

1057
01:20:37,478 --> 01:20:39,673
But not before he told me.

1058
01:20:44,818 --> 01:20:46,649
Maybe he was wrong.

1059
01:20:49,621 --> 01:20:56,117
I mean, this is supposed to be
Cullen territory.

1060
01:20:57,214 --> 01:21:01,150
We've been tearing it up
and I've never even seen them here.

1061
01:21:02,217 --> 01:21:03,980
You don't trust me.

1062
01:21:05,194 --> 01:21:09,723
With my life. I'm just saying...
I'm doing this for us.

1063
01:21:09,754 --> 01:21:14,817
So that we can feed
without their retaliation.

1064
01:21:15,016 --> 01:21:18,782
I can't live in fear anymore,
waiting for them to attack.

1065
01:21:18,853 --> 01:21:20,548
I won't let them.

1066
01:21:21,723 --> 01:21:26,490
I am going to end the Cullen clan.

1067
01:21:29,364 --> 01:21:30,763
I swear.

1068
01:21:47,949 --> 01:21:51,282
I love you so much.

1069
01:22:11,907 --> 01:22:13,306
You're going overboard.

1070
01:22:13,909 --> 01:22:16,469
If this is all I can contribute,
I wanna be thorough.

1071
01:22:16,545 --> 01:22:18,775
The new borns'll be frantic.

1072
01:22:20,983 --> 01:22:24,384
It's okay.
Don't make yourself uncomfortable.

1073
01:22:24,453 --> 01:22:25,784
It doesn't bother me anymore.

1074
01:22:27,890 --> 01:22:29,084
Since when?

1075
01:22:29,558 --> 01:22:32,584
Since I spent 24 hours
thinking you were dead.

1076
01:22:34,230 --> 01:22:36,460
You're not wearing your ring.

1077
01:22:37,967 --> 01:22:40,333
Well, I didn't want to risk losing it.

1078
01:22:42,204 --> 01:22:43,694
Or risk Jacob seeing it.

1079
01:22:46,943 --> 01:22:50,845
I think we should wait to tell him.
I mean, at least till after the fight.

1080
01:22:50,914 --> 01:22:53,542
If you're having second thoughts...
I'm not.

1081
01:22:53,617 --> 01:22:57,713
I just want him to have a clear head.
Whose head is unclear?

1082
01:22:59,256 --> 01:23:00,951
Nobody's I hope.

1083
01:23:01,958 --> 01:23:04,927
Alice says there's a storm coming.
Yeah, I can feel it.

1084
01:23:06,163 --> 01:23:07,960
We should get going.

1085
01:23:09,099 --> 01:23:11,567
I'll see you in a couple of hours.

1086
01:23:20,844 --> 01:23:22,311
Something up?

1087
01:23:25,248 --> 01:23:28,945
Bunch of vampires trying to kill me.
Same old same old.

1088
01:24:46,837 --> 01:24:47,929
Thank you.

1089
01:24:50,438 --> 01:24:52,253
You should get back
before the storm hits.

1090
01:24:52,284 --> 01:24:53,528
No, I'm staying.

1091
01:24:54,304 --> 01:24:57,065
You'll need my connection to the pack
to keep tabs on what's going on.

1092
01:24:57,096 --> 01:25:00,623
You're not gonna fight?
Seth will spell me in the morning.

1093
01:25:01,113 --> 01:25:04,048
He's not happy about missing the action
but it'll keep him out of trouble.

1094
01:25:05,661 --> 01:25:07,219
Let's get you inside.

1095
01:25:20,567 --> 01:25:22,000
(WHIMPERING)

1096
01:25:25,572 --> 01:25:30,737
I should have chosen a site lower down.
No, it's fine. I'm okay.

1097
01:25:31,411 --> 01:25:33,003
What can I do?

1098
01:25:38,885 --> 01:25:40,352
(WIND HOWLING)

1099
01:25:45,758 --> 01:25:49,057
I can't sleep
with all that teeth chattering going on.

1100
01:25:56,336 --> 01:26:00,569
Forget it.
She may need her toes someday.

1101
01:26:01,842 --> 01:26:05,175
And let's face it, I am hotter than you.

1102
01:26:10,251 --> 01:26:15,120
Get your hand off me.
Keep your hands off her.

1103
01:26:15,623 --> 01:26:17,113
Don't fight.

1104
01:26:20,494 --> 01:26:22,291
If she gets sick, it's on you.

1105
01:26:39,346 --> 01:26:41,541
Wow, you're freezing, Bella.

1106
01:26:42,650 --> 01:26:46,108
Relax. You'll warm up soon.

1107
01:26:47,688 --> 01:26:50,249
Faster if you took your clothes off.

1108
01:26:50,325 --> 01:26:52,987
Jake.
Survival 101.

1109
01:27:24,693 --> 01:27:27,924
Can you at least attempt
to control your thoughts?

1110
01:27:30,332 --> 01:27:33,927
I really get under
that ice-cold skin of yours, don't I?

1111
01:27:36,271 --> 01:27:37,398
What?

1112
01:27:38,441 --> 01:27:41,103
Are you doubting her feelings for you?

1113
01:27:43,779 --> 01:27:44,871
Nice.

1114
01:27:46,015 --> 01:27:51,351
So picking through my brain's okay,
but letting me into yours, forget it.

1115
01:27:55,358 --> 01:27:56,518
Look.

1116
01:27:58,094 --> 01:28:00,961
I know she's in love with you.
Good.

1117
01:28:01,631 --> 01:28:03,963
But she's in love with me, too.

1118
01:28:06,202 --> 01:28:08,727
She just won't admit it to herself.

1119
01:28:11,741 --> 01:28:14,175
I can't tell if you're right.

1120
01:28:15,645 --> 01:28:17,169
Then let me ask you something.

1121
01:28:18,247 --> 01:28:20,977
If she chooses me...
She won't.

1122
01:28:21,550 --> 01:28:22,881
If she did,

1123
01:28:24,620 --> 01:28:26,019
would you try to kill me?

1124
01:28:27,658 --> 01:28:29,751
That's an intriguing idea.

1125
01:28:34,665 --> 01:28:37,793
But, no. I couldn't hurt her like that.

1126
01:28:38,935 --> 01:28:41,699
So you'd just turn her into
a blood-sucking demon like you?

1127
01:28:42,506 --> 01:28:45,407
I don't want that. I never wanted that.

1128
01:28:45,842 --> 01:28:48,367
So stop her.
I tried.

1129
01:28:50,180 --> 01:28:52,910
I left.
But you gave up too quickly.

1130
01:28:54,851 --> 01:28:59,754
If you'd stayed away another 6 months,
I could've made her happy.

1131
01:29:00,524 --> 01:29:01,855
Trust me.

1132
01:29:03,360 --> 01:29:08,195
You have to consider that I might
be better for her than you are.

1133
01:29:10,867 --> 01:29:12,801
I have considered that.

1134
01:29:16,507 --> 01:29:18,668
I know you can protect her.

1135
01:29:21,312 --> 01:29:26,147
But you can give her a life, a human life.
That's all I want for her.

1136
01:29:29,320 --> 01:29:30,378
But I'm not...

1137
01:29:31,456 --> 01:29:34,721
I'm not going to force her into anything
ever again.

1138
01:29:37,161 --> 01:29:40,494
The last time I tried,
it almost killed us both.

1139
01:29:42,834 --> 01:29:45,234
Yeah. That I remember.

1140
01:29:49,474 --> 01:29:51,738
When you thought she was gone,

1141
01:29:54,078 --> 01:29:55,841
that you'd lost her,

1142
01:29:58,349 --> 01:30:01,250
how did you cope?

1143
01:30:03,254 --> 01:30:05,052
There are no words.

1144
01:30:11,096 --> 01:30:13,530
But I wouldn't wish it on anyone, Jacob.

1145
01:30:16,268 --> 01:30:19,795
This might sound odd,
but I'm glad you're here.

1146
01:30:20,672 --> 01:30:21,969
Meaning,

1147
01:30:23,008 --> 01:30:25,977
"As much as I'd love to kill you,
I'm glad she's warm."

1148
01:30:29,114 --> 01:30:31,412
If we weren't natural enemies

1149
01:30:31,950 --> 01:30:34,885
and you weren't trying to
steal my reason for existing,

1150
01:30:36,255 --> 01:30:38,382
I might actually like you.

1151
01:30:39,424 --> 01:30:40,721
Well,

1152
01:30:42,294 --> 01:30:46,492
if you weren't planning on sucking the life
out of the girl I love,

1153
01:30:47,399 --> 01:30:48,730
I might...

1154
01:30:55,809 --> 01:30:58,869
No. Not even then.

1155
01:31:07,220 --> 01:31:10,519
But she could still change her mind,
you know.

1156
01:31:17,297 --> 01:31:18,662
Then I'd let her go.

1157
01:31:38,818 --> 01:31:40,410
Right. Hey, Seth.

1158
01:31:43,624 --> 01:31:46,559
Where's Jacob? Did he already...
Not yet.

1159
01:31:48,429 --> 01:31:52,195
He's checking to see if the woods are clear
before he goes.

1160
01:31:59,306 --> 01:32:02,867
I'm really sorry about last night.
That couldn't have been easy on you.

1161
01:32:03,310 --> 01:32:06,302
It definitely won't make my list
of top 10 favorite evenings.

1162
01:32:07,381 --> 01:32:11,511
You have a list?
All 10 I spent with you.

1163
01:32:12,953 --> 01:32:17,322
Number one is when you said
you'd marry me, Mrs. Cullen.

1164
01:32:21,161 --> 01:32:25,063
This is the 21st century.
I at least want to hyphenate my name.

1165
01:32:25,900 --> 01:32:29,358
You're marrying him?
Jake, I...

1166
01:32:33,742 --> 01:32:37,200
You knew he was listening!
He deserves to know.

1167
01:32:38,580 --> 01:32:40,138
Jake, stop!
Bella, let him...

1168
01:32:40,248 --> 01:32:41,374
Don't!

1169
01:32:44,452 --> 01:32:45,510
Jake, stop!

1170
01:32:49,190 --> 01:32:52,648
BELLA: Jake, please!
I'm done! I'm so done!

1171
01:32:53,895 --> 01:32:55,123
What can I do?

1172
01:32:55,196 --> 01:32:59,394
You can't do anything. I can,
by going out there and killing something.

1173
01:32:59,467 --> 01:33:02,061
No! You're not thinking clearly!
Don't do that!

1174
01:33:02,270 --> 01:33:04,932
Maybe I'll get myself killed
and make it simple for you.

1175
01:33:05,006 --> 01:33:07,440
No! Just, Jake, stay.

1176
01:33:09,344 --> 01:33:10,538
Why?

1177
01:33:12,414 --> 01:33:14,109
Give me one good reason.

1178
01:33:15,250 --> 01:33:17,184
Because I don't wanna lose you.

1179
01:33:18,820 --> 01:33:20,186
It's not good enough.

1180
01:33:21,590 --> 01:33:23,455
Because you're too important.

1181
01:33:26,896 --> 01:33:30,388
Still not good enough.
Jacob!

1182
01:33:34,637 --> 01:33:35,899
Kiss me.

1183
01:33:39,275 --> 01:33:42,733
I'm asking you to kiss me.

1184
01:34:30,527 --> 01:34:33,155
That should have been our first kiss.

1185
01:34:38,769 --> 01:34:40,168
I gotta go.

1186
01:34:43,106 --> 01:34:44,505
I'll be back.

1187
01:35:14,739 --> 01:35:18,140
You saw.
No, but...

1188
01:35:19,143 --> 01:35:20,906
Jacob's thoughts are pretty loud.

1189
01:35:22,447 --> 01:35:23,971
I don't know what happened.

1190
01:35:25,983 --> 01:35:27,416
You love him.

1191
01:35:31,823 --> 01:35:33,620
I love you more.

1192
01:35:35,359 --> 01:35:36,724
I know.

1193
01:35:40,098 --> 01:35:41,531
(GRUNTING)

1194
01:35:47,940 --> 01:35:49,305
(GROWLING)

1195
01:35:51,410 --> 01:35:53,139
It's starting.

1196
01:36:19,471 --> 01:36:21,302
(ALL YELLING)

1197
01:36:26,011 --> 01:36:27,342
(ALL GRUNTING)

1198
01:36:31,583 --> 01:36:32,709
(GROWLING)

1199
01:36:53,072 --> 01:36:54,300
Jacob just got there.

1200
01:37:00,747 --> 01:37:02,271
He's good.

1201
01:37:03,616 --> 01:37:05,015
(ALL GRUNTING)

1202
01:37:41,255 --> 01:37:42,255
(GROANS)

1203
01:38:00,574 --> 01:38:01,700
Someone's hurt?

1204
01:38:03,110 --> 01:38:06,136
She's close. I can hear her thoughts.

1205
01:38:06,547 --> 01:38:07,775
Seth, go.

1206
01:38:12,754 --> 01:38:15,120
She knew we weren't there,
but she caught my scent.

1207
01:38:15,590 --> 01:38:17,683
She knew you'd be with me.

1208
01:38:18,326 --> 01:38:19,793
She found us.

1209
01:38:23,398 --> 01:38:25,059
She's not alone.

1210
01:38:34,209 --> 01:38:37,007
Riley, listen to me.

1211
01:38:38,446 --> 01:38:41,506
Victoria's just using you to distract me.

1212
01:38:42,284 --> 01:38:43,751
She knows I'll kill you.

1213
01:38:47,422 --> 01:38:51,188
In fact, she'll be glad
she doesn't have to deal with you anymore.

1214
01:38:51,860 --> 01:38:56,229
Don't listen, Riley.
I told you about their mind tricks.

1215
01:38:56,298 --> 01:39:00,132
I can read her mind.
So I know what she thinks of you.

1216
01:39:00,635 --> 01:39:02,297
VICTORIA: He's lying.

1217
01:39:02,371 --> 01:39:07,035
She only created you and this army
to avenge her true mate, James.

1218
01:39:08,210 --> 01:39:11,338
That's the only thing she cares about.
Not you.

1219
01:39:13,983 --> 01:39:17,441
There's only you. You know that.

1220
01:39:19,855 --> 01:39:23,518
Think about it. You're from Forks.

1221
01:39:25,428 --> 01:39:26,588
You know the area.

1222
01:39:27,697 --> 01:39:29,562
That's the only reason she chose you.

1223
01:39:31,267 --> 01:39:33,497
She doesn't love you.

1224
01:39:33,569 --> 01:39:38,563
Riley. Don't let him do this to us.

1225
01:39:41,010 --> 01:39:42,477
You know I love you.

1226
01:39:56,660 --> 01:39:58,059
You're dead.

1227
01:40:01,098 --> 01:40:02,759
(GROWLING)

1228
01:40:08,772 --> 01:40:09,966
(HOWLING)

1229
01:40:12,709 --> 01:40:15,109
You won't get another chance
like this again.

1230
01:40:19,449 --> 01:40:20,939
You want her.

1231
01:40:22,753 --> 01:40:25,984
You want me to feel the pain you felt
when I killed James,

1232
01:40:28,125 --> 01:40:30,787
when I tore him to pieces,

1233
01:40:33,296 --> 01:40:35,992
when I turned him into ash,

1234
01:40:38,168 --> 01:40:42,128
when I turned him into nothing.

1235
01:40:45,443 --> 01:40:46,774
(ROARING)

1236
01:41:15,940 --> 01:41:16,940
(GRUNTS)

1237
01:41:21,846 --> 01:41:23,245
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1238
01:41:52,177 --> 01:41:53,303
(GRUNTING)

1239
01:41:58,283 --> 01:41:59,477
(GROWLING)

1240
01:42:02,254 --> 01:42:03,414
Victoria!

1241
01:42:04,857 --> 01:42:06,051
Victoria!

1242
01:42:06,925 --> 01:42:08,517
Victoria!

1243
01:42:11,663 --> 01:42:12,857
(GRUNTING)

1244
01:42:58,211 --> 01:43:00,008
(LOW GROWLING)

1245
01:43:02,649 --> 01:43:05,584
Something is wrong.
Alice needs us to go.

1246
01:43:06,520 --> 01:43:07,612
Now.

1247
01:43:30,644 --> 01:43:33,704
EDWARD: How long?
A few minutes. Maybe 10?

1248
01:43:33,781 --> 01:43:35,146
DR. CULLEN: The pack needs to leave.

1249
01:43:35,215 --> 01:43:37,706
The Volturi won't honor
a truce with the werewolves.

1250
01:43:42,690 --> 01:43:43,690
(SNARLS)

1251
01:43:44,692 --> 01:43:45,750
Leah, don't!

1252
01:44:03,044 --> 01:44:04,739
Jacob!

1253
01:44:08,116 --> 01:44:10,676
Jacob. Hold on.
Carlisle's gonna take care of you.

1254
01:44:10,752 --> 01:44:12,913
The bones on the right half of his body
are shattered.

1255
01:44:14,656 --> 01:44:17,022
Bella.
Jake, I'm right here.

1256
01:44:19,027 --> 01:44:21,291
Jacob, you idiot, I had it!
Leah!

1257
01:44:21,363 --> 01:44:24,025
I need to set the bones
before his accelerated healing kicks in.

1258
01:44:24,099 --> 01:44:26,397
It's already starting.
EDWARD: We need to get him out of here.

1259
01:44:26,468 --> 01:44:29,335
We're not gonna win a fight
with the Volturi.

1260
01:44:29,404 --> 01:44:32,134
We'll take him back to Billy's.
I'll be there soon as I can.

1261
01:44:32,674 --> 01:44:33,732
Hang in there, Jake.

1262
01:44:41,416 --> 01:44:42,713
(GROANING)

1263
01:44:44,487 --> 01:44:47,251
It's okay. We got you.
We got you.

1264
01:44:48,224 --> 01:44:49,350
They're coming.

1265
01:45:10,913 --> 01:45:12,175
Impressive.

1266
01:45:12,248 --> 01:45:16,810
JANE: I've never seen a coven escape
an assault of this magnitude intact.

1267
01:45:16,886 --> 01:45:18,444
We were lucky.

1268
01:45:19,922 --> 01:45:21,514
I doubt that.

1269
01:45:23,426 --> 01:45:25,484
It appears we missed
an entertaining fight.

1270
01:45:25,515 --> 01:45:26,914
JANE: Yes.

1271
01:45:27,418 --> 01:45:30,080
It's not often we're rendered unnecessary.

1272
01:45:30,139 --> 01:45:32,979
If you'd arrived a half hour ago,
you would have fulfilled your purpose.

1273
01:45:34,517 --> 01:45:35,677
Pity.

1274
01:45:39,551 --> 01:45:41,109
You missed one.

1275
01:45:48,081 --> 01:45:50,515
We offered her asylum
in exchange for her surrender.

1276
01:45:51,897 --> 01:45:53,660
That wasn't yours to offer.

1277
01:45:56,927 --> 01:45:58,053
Why did you come?

1278
01:45:59,414 --> 01:46:01,984
(SCREAMING)

1279
01:46:04,401 --> 01:46:05,629
Who created you?

1280
01:46:05,869 --> 01:46:07,425
(SCREAMING)

1281
01:46:07,471 --> 01:46:10,191
You don't need to do that.
She'll tell you anything you want to know.

1282
01:46:10,777 --> 01:46:12,039
I know.

1283
01:46:14,154 --> 01:46:18,022
I don't know! Riley wouldn't tell us.

